## Comparative Overview of Rousseau’s Influence

| Aspect                      | Rousseau’s Philosophy                          | Revolutionary Application                     | Outcome/Impact                              |
|-----------------------------|-----------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------|
| **Political Authority**      | Popular sovereignty; government by general will | National Assembly and popular participation | Overthrow of monarchy; rise of republic     |
| **Equality**                 | Equality through social contract; critique of private property | Abolition of feudal privileges; redistribution efforts | Social reforms; economic tensions           |
| **Liberty**                  | Natural freedom surrendered for collective good | Declaration of Rights; civil liberties asserted | Expansion of rights; later repression       |
| **Government Form**          | Small republics; direct democracy preferred   | Attempts at representative democracy; Jacobin rule | Political instability; authoritarianism     |
| **Use of Force**             | Legitimate only if aligned with general will  | Reign of Terror justified by general will    | Terror and suppression of dissent            |

